entries.femaleVariant: Looking for Booker Updike.
You work here?
Don't make angry.
Sure, doesn't matter.
Privacy as a service, huh? How much you charge for that? Somethin' like this? Maybe more?
Sure, come with me, but keep it down, 'ey?
[Bribe]
Yeah, see, think you misheard me. Wasn't a question, wasn't a request.
Uhh... B-but...
Hey, look at me. Right in the eyes. Choose your next words carefully, choomba. Might be the last choice you ever make.
Oh, OK, OK... Um, come with me. B-but please keep it down.
Right. 'K, see ya.
I was never here, got it?
Little... little bit more.
Open his room for me.
OK, thanks, see ya.
Open up his room for me.
Yo, I just said privacy's kinda our thing here. He'll come out if he wants to come out, OK?
Hey, you work here?
Psh, nah. Just fuckin' takin' in the sights.
Lookin' for a friend. Booker Updike.
Wait a sec, that, uh... He a tall, white guy? Kinda keeps to himself, yeah?
Well, he's been locked up in his room. Don't ever come out. Not even for coffee in the A.M.
But, hey, customer is king, right? He wants peace an' quiet, we give it to 'im. No questions.
Could be. Haven't seen each other in a while... What makes you say that?
Asked you nicely. Should I ask another way?
All right, all right. No need getting worked up. Yeah, I work maintenance. Plumber, electrician, bit of ev'rything.
Done. Now open the room. And be quick.
